[22:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'maybe we this can start when the robot kind of comes alive. I will see. I\'ll keep it there. Let\'s just search for gizmo. That\'s a nice phrase. That\'s nice. I like the hydraulics in'

[22:34] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'there. Let\'s try this for like the startup sound. Yeah, we can get rid of this for now. You can probably recognize some of these'

[22:46] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'sounds. These are from Yeah, if you can recognize what video these sounds are from, it\'s I\'ve used it I know exactly what animation I\'ve used it in. So, if you can remember that, please leave a'

[22:58] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'comment. Here\'s the sound. Yeah, if you can remember that, I\'ll be very impressed. So, please leave a comment if you know that. That\'s a cool robot sound. However,'

[23:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'important note if you\'re working with DaVinci Resolve, here you can see that this is only one line of sounds, right? So, if you take this and you drag it onto the timeline, we\'re only going to be able to hear it in one ear.'

[23:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'You hear that? Left channel. And that is because this is like a mono sound effect. So, the way to fix this, if you hold your mouse here and press J, now you have it basically faked into becoming a stereo sound. So, now you can'

[23:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'take it and you can pull it in here and you will hear it in both both ears. And also, just a quick tip, if you have imported an audio file that was mono and you want to hear it in both ears, you can right-click, clip attributes, and go'

[23:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to audio, and you can set the format to stereo, and then you set embedded channel one to be on both left and right channel. It should look like this. Now, if you click okay, it should be in both ears. Yeah, I wanted to open up with like this.'

